#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_copy_base.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._copy_base.BaseCopy.set_types:1
msgid "Set the types expected in a COPY operation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_copy_base.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._copy_base.BaseCopy.set_types:3
msgid ""
"The types must be specified as a sequence of oid or PostgreSQL type names (e."
"g. ``int4``, ``timestamptz[]``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_copy_base.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._copy_base.BaseCopy.set_types:6
msgid ""
"This operation overcomes the lack of metadata returned by PostgreSQL when a "
"COPY operation begins:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_copy_base.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._copy_base.BaseCopy.set_types:9
msgid ""
"On :sql:`COPY TO`, `!set_types()` allows to specify what types the operation "
"returns. If `!set_types()` is not used, the data will be returned as "
"unparsed strings or bytes instead of Python objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/_copy_base.py:docstring
#: of psycopg._copy_base.BaseCopy.set_types:13
msgid ""
"On :sql:`COPY FROM`, `!set_types()` allows to choose what type the database "
"expects. This is especially useful in binary copy, because PostgreSQL will "
"apply no cast rule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/copy.rst:43
msgid ""
"The object is normally returned by ``async with`` `AsyncCursor.copy()`. Its "
"methods are similar to the ones of the `Copy` object but offering an "
"`asyncio` interface (`await`, `async for`, `async with`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/copy.rst:51
msgid ""
"Instead of using `!read()` you can iterate on the `!AsyncCopy` object to "
"read its data row by row, using ``async for row in copy: ...``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/copy.rst:56
msgid "Use it as `async for record in copy.rows():` ..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/copy.rst:64
msgid "Writer objects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/copy.rst:70
msgid ""
"Copy writers are helper objects to specify where to write COPY-formatted "
"data. By default, data is written to the database (using the `LibpqWriter`). "
"It is possible to write copy-data for offline use by using a `FileWriter`, "
"or to customize further writing by implementing your own `Writer` or "
"`AsyncWriter` subclass."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/copy.rst:76
msgid ""
"Writers instances can be used passing them to the cursor `~psycopg.Cursor."
"copy()` method or to the `~psycopg.Copy` constructor, as the `!writer` "
"argument."
msgstr ""

